stix:STIX_Header.stix:Title: IB-20-10301 IOCs Related to Ransomware Operations Impacting Multiple Sectors
stix:STIX_Header.stix:Description:
On October 30, 2020, Crowdstrike Threat Intelligence shared indicators of compromise (IOCs) with CISA that were associated with a threat actor they refer to as Wizard Spider. These IOCs are associated with TrickBot, Emotet/Geodo, and BazarLoader malware and have been used in support of ransomware operations. Much of this activity was observed from September to October 2020,  while some attacks dated back to April 2020.

This activity was reported in the Information Technology Sector and observed across multiple sectors.
